Document: MeshConvexDecompositionSettings
Path: godot/classes/class_meshconvexdecompositionsettings.rst
Summary: Provides settings for convex decomposition of meshes.

Inherits: Resource < RefCounted < Object

This class holds settings for the convex decomposition of a mesh. It's used by the `Mesh.convex_decomposition()` method.

Properties:

mesh_path (String): The path to the mesh resource to decompose.
max_concavity (float): The maximum concavity allowed. A lower value results in more, smaller convex shapes. Default: 2.0.
max_iterations (int): The maximum number of iterations to perform. A higher value can lead to better results but takes longer. Default: 100.
voxel_size (float): The size of the voxels to use for the decomposition. A smaller voxel size can capture finer details but increases computation time. Default: 0.01.
merge_clipping (bool): Whether to merge clipping planes. This can help reduce the number of convex shapes. Default: false.
merge_neutral_islands (bool): Whether to merge neutral islands. This can help reduce the number of convex shapes. Default: true.
merge_ghost_cliques (bool): Whether to merge ghost cliques. This can help reduce the number of convex shapes. Default: true.
max_convex_hulls (int): The maximum number of convex hulls to generate. Default: 4.
alpha (float): The alpha value for the decomposition. Default: 0.95.
beta (float): The beta value for the decomposition. Default: 0.01.
theta (float): The theta value for the decomposition. Default: 0.01.
pca_normalize (bool): Whether to normalize the PCA. Default: false.
convexhull_downsampling (bool): Whether to downsample the convex hull. Default: false.
ocd_simplify_hulls (bool): Whether to simplify the hulls using OCD. Default: false.
add_unnamed_polygon_models_to_all_islands (bool): Whether to add unnamed polygon models to all islands. Default: false.
min_volume_per_hull (float): The minimum volume per hull. Default: 0.0001.
callback (String): The callback function to call during decomposition. Default: "".
