Document: MeshConvexDecompositionSettings
Path: godot/classes/class_meshconvexdecompositionsettings.rst
Summary: Describes the properties available for configuring convex decomposition settings in Godot.

Property: convex_hull_approximation (bool)
Description: If true, uses approximation for computing convex hulls.
Default: true

Property: convex_hull_downsampling (int)
Description: Controls the precision of the convex-hull generation process during the clipping plane selection stage. Ranges from 1 to 16.
Default: 4

Property: max_concavity (float)
Description: Maximum concavity. Ranges from 0.0 to 1.0.
Default: 1.0

Property: max_convex_hulls (int)
Description: The maximum number of convex hulls to produce from the merge operation.
Default: 1

Property: max_num_vertices_per_convex_hull (int)
Description: Controls the maximum number of triangles per convex-hull. Ranges from 4 to 1024.
Default: 32

Property: min_volume_per_convex_hull (float)
Description: Controls the adaptive sampling of the generated convex-hulls. Ranges from 0.0 to 0.01.
Default: 0.0001

Property: mode (Mode)
Description: Mode for the approximate convex decomposition.
Default: 0

Property: normalize_mesh (bool)
Description: If true, normalizes the mesh before applying the convex decomposition.
Default: false

Property: plane_downsampling (int)
Description: Controls the granularity of the search for the "best" clipping plane. Ranges from 1 to 16.
Default: 4

Property: project_hull_vertices (bool)
Description: If true, projects output convex hull vertices onto the original source mesh to increase floating-point accuracy of the results.
Default: true

Property: resolution (int)
Description: Maximum number of voxels generated during the voxelization stage.
Default: 10000

Property: revolution_axes_clipping_bias (float)
Description: Controls the bias toward clipping along revolution axes. Ranges from 0.0 to 1.0.
Default: 0.05

Property: symmetry_planes_clipping_bias (float)
Description: Controls the bias toward clipping along symmetry planes. Ranges from 0.0 to 1.0.
Default: 0.05